<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4134450>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Hornera frondiculata (Lamarck, 1816), frontal side: A, part of colony with five bifurcations; B, growing tip of a branch; C, initial stage of secondary calcification with ridges encircling autozooids with typically notched peristomes and frontal wall pierced with large mural pores; D, intermediate stage of secondary calcification; E, older stage of secondary calcification;F, part of colony with several lateral branches.Origin:A-D, Greece, Scarpanto Strait,29-33 m,29.VIII.1967; E, Marseille, Riou Is., 70 m, 3.VII.1971; F, Riou Is., 90 m, 2.III.1972. Scale bars: A, F, 500 µm; B, 200 µm; C-D, 100 m; E, 150 µm. Photos:Jean-Georges Harmelin." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4134450/files/figure.png" .

