<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4134452>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — Hornera frondiculata (Lamarck, 1816), dorsal side: A, part of colony with 2 gonozooids; B, gonozooid lateral view showing the ooeciostome and the basal tube; C, frontal view of a gonozooid chamber under construction; D, gonozooid wall made of foliated crystallites and mural pore closed by radial spines; E, wall of dorsal side with ridges delimiting porous spindle-shaped areas. Origin: A-E, Marseille, Riou Is., 70 m, 3.VII.1971. Scale bars: A-B, 500 µm; C, 250 µm; D, 5 µm; E, 200 µm. Photos: Jean-Georges Harmelin." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4134452/files/figure.png" .

